latestPosts.caption:
Taylour Gonzales ✨💜
Licensed Cosmetologist💇🏾‍♀️
Certified Trichologist🌱

Allow my to reintroduce myself! I’ve been a Cosmetologist for 10 years now. My main goal has ALWAYS been healthy hair. From styling natural hair, silk presses, educating my clients and social media, also encouraging my clients to use quality products outside the salon. 

One think I’ve noticed is that lots of women that look like me are experiencing hair loss and scalp conditions. So I decided to take a course to become a Trichologist. This has really helped me and expanded my knowledge on hair care. I always wanted to know the “why’s”. This course taught me why. It’s our diet, products, lifestyle, hairstyles, hormones, genetics, and etc. As a Trichologist, I want to help people achieve a healthy scalp! A healthy scalp is the start for healthy hair.

I’m super excited to take this pivot in my career. I can’t wait to start offering my Trichology services. Make sure you’re subscribed to my newsletter to find out when my Trichology services will be available online! ✨💜

‼️YOUR APPOINTMENT SHOULD START AT THE BOWL IF YOUR SERVICE PROVIDER IS LICENSED‼️

A good shampoo and scalp examination is required in my salon. This helps me tailor my shampoo service to my clients needs. Also, I inform my clients on treatments they may need, and it lets me know where they are in their hair journey. Don’t cheat your clients or yourself out of good results ✨💜#hairbytanngee #hairbytanngeestimulatingoil #certifiedtrichologist #trichologist🌱 #sdstylist🌴 #sandiegohairstylist #healthyhairstylistsandiego #healthyhairstylist #healthyhairstylist #sandiegocontentcreator

Some of my FAVORITE products in the salon right now have been from brands like Mizani, Olaplex, Kenra! Although product is important, technique is MORE important. 

I always recommend working in sections. It helps with proper Detangling AND prevents mechanical damage. Remember when working with textured hair, you have to be delicate and intentional. Our hair is our crown.
